YO_ngkGvdFKjiQmIP89YZQ
I was excited to try this place out. My wife and I raced with another 12 or so people on the track. We were not able to get in a single full lap in without everyone either getting slowed or completely stopped. My wife and I saw the usual amount of "bumping" in the corners but no one seemed to be malicious about it or taking the race way too seriously.   I'm all for safety and taking these measures when you get "that one guy" on the track but they were nazis about every little thing people seemed to do. They even came over and talked sternly to some of the racers.   The constant interruptions robbed racers of momentum, pace, and more importantly fun. It wasn't a pleasant experience so we will not be going back. Such a pity because it's a really cool environment.   Pros: Super nice facility, Nice equipment, Check in was easy,  Cons: Very expensive, Staff are indifferent, Race staff are Nazis.  My experience: I've gokarted in Germany, Switzerland, Turkey, England, California, Texas, and South Carolina for over 20 years.

