This is the best sushi for your dollar in Phoenix. Don't get me wrong there are better sushi joints in the valley that have better environments, better sushi and in rare cases both, but none have it for this price.   I've been here a few times and each experience the staff goes over and above to keep us fat and happy, and with how good the food is, its not that hard.   If your mango fan, I would recommend the Golden Dragon Roll.  Cost: Cheap Quality: 4 out of 5 Staff: 5 out of 5  Enjoy this little gem.

